<TITLE> Zakat theft probe report on Jul 11 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 25 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court has set July 11 as the date for submitting the investigation report on alleged misappropriation of zakat money by former Jamaat-e-Islami MP Delwar Hossain Sayedee and former state minister for religious affairs Mosharraf Hossain Shahjahan. The Islamic Foundation has filed a case against the two men for embezzling over Tk 10 million in zakat funds. Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate Court's judge Dilara Alo Chandana fixed the date on Tuesday. Abdur Rashid, an official of the Anticorruption Commission, under Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrates Court, confirmed the date to bdnews24.com. Islamic Foundation's director (finance and accounts) Ayub Ali Chowdhury filed the case with the Sher-e-Bangla Nagar Police Station on Monday noon. The case details said the duo embezzled the funds in 2004-2005 fiscal year by allocating the money in annual charity tax to the organisation of their choice. Sayedee was chairman of the parliamentary standing committee on religious affairs ministry. bdnews
